name: Stay Over @Entertainment Core.

reviews.comments: Place is awesome in terms of location and it pretty much everything included to kick start but at times it becomes difficult to communicate with the host!

Me and my partner booked to stay for one month and when we checked in to the apartment, honestly we were a bit disappointed. The size of the apartment was not up to what we expected that the floor plan was absurd to us. The kitchen and living room was so small while the bed room is relatively spacious in comparison. Good thing is we find the bed room pretty spacious and cozy, with a small desk area available to study or work from home.
For someone who loves to cook like me, I find it frustrated see how small the kitchen was and how limited the utensils were provided. Pots and pans were dirty and old, in fact we needed to buy some new pots and pans to cook for ourselves because the one provided were not usable.
Another thing is the response time for the host is unreasonably long most of the time...we hope he can improve on that.
Good point for this place is the location. There are lots of restaurants and bars around and accessible to street cars and subway. However it is hard to find a nice grocery store around and the price is very expensive.
In our opinion it could be an option for tight-budgeted travelers who want to stay in the center of downtown and explore the city, just to stay for a couple days or up to a week but unfortunately we would not book with this apartment again and would not recommend for a long-term stay like our case.

Great place to stay and very comfortable. Had a very minor issue at first, which was promptly resolved by Rajeeb.
Location is also excellent, and near everything you may need (there are a couple of constructions in front of it, but the noise wasn’t too bothersome).
Wonderfull host. Attentative and very helpful. 5 stars all around. location is great. Everything that you need is available.
Recommend!

My husband and I love staying in Rajeeb's apartment. The apartment is perfect for a couple and has all items that you need for a long stay.
The building is very located, near to all you need and the gym and pool are excellent.
Great place easy access easy everything
Great stay in all regards except that host is sometimes slow to communicate back.

Great location and (26th floor) view from the balcony.  Good bathroom (shower & bath) v comfortable bed and decent linen.  Lots of hanging space, no dresser.   The host was easy to connect with and check in & out was a breeze. I told the host the desk is to small for COVID working and the kitchen/dining table not great. I’m sure he’ll fix this.

I took this place in Nov since I was arriving in Canada an needed a place to quarantine. This spot was great, fully self contained, new building, balcony, internet, computer desk etc. When I finally got out after 14 days I realized there is everything you need in walking distance, a bulk bran, shoppers, transport, grocery. The only thing is there is construction being done in the area so during the day you will hear the sound from that otherwise. Cool spot in the city.

sectionedDescription.description:
Located in the heart of downtown on a high floor. A sun filled suite with floor to ceiling windows, Ideally located in the heart of Toronto's World Class Entertainment District and just minutes from the CN Tower, Ripley's Aquarium, Rogers Centre, Metro Convention Centre, TIFF Bell Light Box, Union Station, Restaurants, Bars,Pubs, Theatres, Shopping, Grocery store, Cafes and more!

Incredibly appointed, this luxury suite features high end finishes throughout, Queen sized extra-comfy bed in the bedroom, amazing views, a balcony, private washroom and a full kitchen.

Guests can use pool and fitness.

Text me @ (PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN)

This is to let you know how things are organized in your new home.
Bath mats, face towels, hand towels and Bath towels are at the top of the left closet beside the main entrance. You will also find vacuum cleaner and steam mop in it. Beside this closet there is washer and Dryer. On the top of the dryer there are Paper towels and laundry detergent for the washer. Beside this there is refrigerator.
On the kitchen counter there are paper towels, smoothie maker, toaster, coffee maker and electric kettle.
In the first left drawer there are knifes, scissor and cutleries. In the drawers below that there are cooking utensils.
In the cabinet below the sink there is organic garbage bin, plastics for bin, dish detergents. In the right of this there are extra kitchen towels and first aid kit.
In the top kitchen cabinets there are plates and glasses, coffee, tea and sugar.
In washroom on the sink there are face soap, body soap and shampoo and in the cabinet below the washroom sink there are extra toilet papers.
On the top of the bedroom closet there are extra bed sheets, Duvet cover, pillow covers and pillows. Outside the apartment on left side there is garbage disposal.
Let us know if you need anything else. We will be happy to make your stay enjoyable and memorable.
sectionedDescription.houseRules:
No extra guests allowed and please treat this place as your own place.
Check-out is 11am at the latest, and check-in is 4pm - 9pm ONLY, but we can accommodate after hours check in for $50 overtime fee. Guest MUST let us know in advance.

No smoking inside apartment. Smoking outside on balcony ONLY making sure butt is disposed in butt bin only.

It is important that all guests treat the unit as if it were their own. No parties are allowed in the condo and only registered guests who have booked the unit on Airbnb are allowed entry to the building and the condo. No pets or smoking in the unit. Please keep noise to a minimum after hours to respect other residents in the building. Thank you!

No parties or large gatherings of people are permitted. Please ask if you have any doubts.

- If there is a noise complaint, you will get 1 warning. After the first warning, if there is another noise complaint, you will be asked to leave the property and your deposit will be forfeited.

Laundry 
You are welcome to use the laundry however please make sure that you check all the pockets and make sure the coins or other small items don't block the drain systems. It does cost a fortune to make a repair and guest are responsible for any expenses.

If you have any questions, you can reach me on my cell at (PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN)

Check in:
1. Please call me at (PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN) or Message me on Airbnb when you are about 15 minutes away before arriving to the condo.

2. The wifi is under Rogers2602 and the password is available at your place.

3. The place will be left professionally cleaned after each guest. The bed sheets and towels are washed before you arrive.

4. The garbage disposal for small garbage is outside the apartment on the left and for big stuff down the hall beside the elevator. Please empty garbage on check out.

5. Please respect and treat the place as your own home.

6. Smoking and Pets is strictly prohibited. A fine up to max of $5000 will be charged to the guest that made the reservation and Host have the right to cancel the reservation immediately without any refunds / notice.

7. $ 500 replacement fee for each set of lost keys/fobs

8. On check out, please confirm with host of your desired check out time. Latest check out is 11 am. Later checkout may be offered for a fee when there is no same day booking.

9. Food Delivery or other delivery: Please meet delivery driver in the Lobby.

I hope you enjoy your stay. If you are new to Toronto, I suggest going for a walk along Front street, there are many things to explore. Toronto has a PATH that connect downtown core building together and you are able to travel from Union Station Building to Toronto Eaton’s Centre without going outside. If you need any assistance, I am always here to assists you anytime. I hope you enjoy your stay. =)

Public parking on property - There is plenty of public parking within 1 min

Cancellations

Strict

Cancel up to 7 days before your trip and get a 50% refund. Cancel within 7 days of your trip and the reservation is non-refundable.

reviews.comments: Griselda & Rob gave us our dream garden wedding! We unfortunately had to change our wedding plans due to Covid and we were so lucky to find this hidden gem! All of our guests were so impressed by how beautiful the space was and Griselda was lovely to work with during the planning process. We would definitely recommend this gorgeous space for your wedding!
A night engraved in our memories forever. We couldn’t have done it without their staff. Wish we could relive this place all over again. Griselda and the entire team were nothing but 5 stars!!!!❤️❤️❤️

We held our cocktail and dinner reception at R Garden Boutique and it was everything we hoped for! Griselda and her team are absolutely amazing! Professional, considerate, accommodating and just wonderful!!

The Garden Retreat is an absolutely beautiful location in the middle of the GTA. My husband and I had a small party for our close friends there, and both Griselda and Rob were a pleasure to work with. If you're looking for a piece of heaven on earth, this is the place to be!
Griselda is hands down the best, she made us feel like family, worked in the background tirelessly to make our day feel special, amazing place and location, worth every penny !

Amazing venue, very stunning, we hosted our wedding here and all our guests were surprised at how beautiful it was. The venue is tucked in a secluded area which gives you and your guests privacy. There's so much space outside where you can enjoy and sit , I wish we took advantage of the night scene but nonetheless this was one of the best venues airbnb has to offer. Robert and Selina were extremely helpful and took care of whatever demands we needed. They went above and beyond to make our experience and wedding a success. I'd definitely recommend this place. 10/10

reviews.comments: This was a great apartment, close to town and restaurants. I was a little worried about parking but Colin was very helpful explaining the permit process for parking on the street, and even printed out our permit for us once we had bought it online. We even managed to park right outside. Both bed and pull-out were very comfy. Thanks Colin!

This location is amazing and sets you up to have THE MOST WONDERFUL time in Toronto. The place is comfortable and clean. Colin was very accommodating and we really appreciated his kind help. The only thing I would say is if you need silence to sleep that may be an issue as you can hear the guests staying in the apartment above and below you. However this shouldn’t stop you from staying, we had a great holiday and didn’t want to leave!

Really nice one bedroom and sleep four people very comfortable. Surprisingly big with lots of natural lighting, makes a real feel at home experience. Really appreciate all the small tools and appliances that were in the kitchen. Made it very easy to make your own food if you don’t feel like eating out. Very close to the downtown area and lots of nice amenities within walking distance. Colin was very friendly and professional!
Excellent place. Super clean. Very responsive and accommodating.

We stayed in Colin's flat for two nights. It is a good place to stay if you are travelling by car as there is parking available, for a small fee overnight, and public transport near the flat to take you downtown. The flat is clean with everything you need. We enjoyed our stay.

Location is a quick walk from many vibrant areas. Lots of store front and the night life in the area is great.
The place itself is very modern and clean. Very spacious and it comfortably sleeps 4 people.
Colin is a great host. Quick response and communication was great. Would definitely rebook this place again if I come back.
Colin's place was just as pictured and very welcoming. Our stay was great and we found that this location was walking distance to many fun activities in downtown Toronto!
Great location!
Nice place in very nice neighbourhood. Awesome and cosy backyard
Colin’s apartment is really lovely. Location is near a 24h supermarket,easy to get groceries.

reviews.comments: Amazing stay!!!
Me and my gf stayed at Shahzars place. Very nice apartment, great location and and very nice view. Comfortable beds .. would highly recommend

Super apartment in the center of Toronto. We appreciate our interactions with Shahzer who was very available at our request. The apartment was the same as the description. Just a little problem with neighbours who considered their lifts as a nightclub until 4 am..

A cute little place! One of the bedrooms is very small, the other a good size. I'd say this apartment can fit 4 people. There's no balcony- but a nice big sliding window that you can view the city from. I didn't ever figure out how to turn the TV on
Easy check in.  Great location. Would recommend to stay
Place is exactly as what’s in the picture.
The place was really nice, highly recommend!

Had a good time in Toronto and a comfortable stay at shahzer’s place. The apartment was perfect for my family and everything was a locates close by. The only hurdle was not having a key fob while entering and entering the building. The security and tenants weren’t very helpful in process, besides this I had a great time. Would recommend if they have entry fobs available.
reviews.response: Jeru thank you for the feedback. The building was under a period where the security systems wasn't being programmed but that has been fixed now and there are no issues with entry. We're sorry this happened so suddenly as they didn't give us any notices. Hope we see you again.

reviews.comments: Very nice place.

Great location and space, looks great in the photos however the place is not well kept. There were uncleaned spots on the sofa, marks and fingerprints on the walls and switches, one of the bed blankets had a large dried up spot from who knows what, the carpet in the bedroom didn't seem to be vacuumed. We felt uncomfortable and were constantly washing our hands, we were almost tempted to hire a proper cleaner to give the place a full refresh. I'm not one to complain but it was honestly unpleasant, if properly cleaned and maintained this would be a truly great place, until then I would not recommend it.
We also had no FOB so we always had to ask concierge to let us in each time we left and came back, that's not necessarily a deal breaker and apparently it was temporary but we weren't informed until after we paid and reserved, we were really looking forward to using the jacuzzi as featured but since we didn't have a FOB we didn't have access and the concierge said it was closed even though a person that lived there said it wasn't, very odd.
Overall it has potential, but feeling grossed out when you just want a nice place to stay and sleep isn't very accomodating, also mentioning the fact that we wouldn't have access to a fob for the doors and jacuzzi the listing before accepting reservations/payments would be ideal.

sectionedDescription.description:
You'll be staying in the heart of Toronto steps away from upscale restaurants and various Toronto attractions within a 5-10 min walk :  

✔wifi ✔gym ✔transit ✔Netflix ✔WhirlPool

+ Toronto Eaton Centre.
+ CN Tower
+ Scotiabank Arena
+ Rogers Centre
+ Ripleys Aquarium 
+ Entertainment District

Experience an upscale condo in Toronto, surrounded by beautiful high rises, downtown architecture, and at the same time have access to transit by your doorstep and explore the rest of the city with ease

You'll be staying in a professionally decorated modern, luxury 2 bedroom 1 bathroom condo apartment. You are located right in the centre of all the action with restaurants, cafes, public transit and all major attractions literally within a 5-20 mins walk.  When not out exploring the city you'll have access to:

+ Fast WiFi + Netflix & TV 
+ Cooking essentials like pots and pans, salt pepper 
+ Utensils, plating and small wares
+ Lounge Room and Gym 
+ Brand new washer and dryer + and more

Parking is available across the street ranging from $18-$25/day.


We also provide hand towels and bath towels for your comfort

Guests are allowed to access the gym which is on the 18th floor.

We are here to help answer questions and can meet in person if requested. The line can be used to call us for emergencies and the air bnb app is our  preferred method for communication so we can provide accurate information.

You are steps away from the CTN tower and Toronto's famous King Street. Transit and subway options are also near by so you don't need to drive anywhere. We strongly recommend transit so you can avoid the traffic and get places much quicker.

Train, Bus and Street car are all outside so you never have to worry about waiting or having to go far to get around. The train is across the street connected to the Eaton Centre which is also a major landmark in Toronto.

- Please no parties or smoking inside the unit. If this is to be found we will have to cancel the reservation without refund.
- Also we strongly recommend you take transit or the subway/train to get around. You are literally in the core of the city so transit is usually much faster than driving. Street busses are right outisde and you can walk to a train station in under 10 mins.
- Please leave all windows closed at all times to avoid bugs and dust from coming inside

reviews.comments: There are no words to describe how perfect our stay was at Jordan's home in Toronto. However, I'm going to try my best to share my experience here. From the moment we booked the home, Jordan went above and beyond to communicate with us in a timely and professional manner. He made the check in and check out process seamless. He was always readily available for any requests or inquiries from my team. The home itself was beyond delightful - the pictures are incredible but the home is even more stunning in person. The way the light comes through the entire house is simply breathtaking and the immaculate decor and layout, truly makes the home one of the most special we've found on Airbnb. I would recommend that every single person stay here if they can - the location is superb, the stay is 5-star and you will be over-the-moon excited with everything Jordan and his team provides.

Jordan’s place was just stunning! More beautiful than the pictures for sure! The team was incredibly responsive and very accommodating. There are several beautiful amenities to take advantage of, and that we did! Fantastic location easily accessible to all major parts in the city. Overall highly recommended as you won’t want to leave!! Thanks for having us :)
Jordan’s place was beautiful..amazing host...great place to stay
You can expect a beautiful modern home in a great area.  Excellent host.
Jordan and his team provided an outstanding experience unlike any other!
Jordan was absolutely fantastic and his place was amazing. I will definitely come back!
Amazing, amazing space. Everything the pictures make it out to be and wonderful hosting service. Used the space for a gathering and it was absolutely fantastic.
Jordan had put together a team of people that will help to make your stay one to remember. The unit is kept in pristine condition and has everything you could need to feel right at home.
Awesome and accommodating!
Thank you for hosting the cup and our family. We could not have found a more perfect place. Beyond expectations!!

sectionedDescription.description:
Heart of Entertainment Distract. Walking distance to transit, dining, movie, shipping, waterfront, and CN Tower and more.

The Space
 
This beautiful downtown condo is located in the vibrant Entertainment District. It is steps from countless fun options, including TIFF Light Box Theatre, Air Canada Centre, Rogers Centre, and the CN Tower. The area is defined by amazing restaurants, upscale nightlife, interesting shops, and a rich multi-cultural lifestyle – the best that Toronto has to offer. We have 2 bedrooms, one with a comfortable large Queen bed and the other with a cozy single bed, as well as an oversized couch in the living room that can be used as an additional bed. Guests are delighted to stay here, in a quiet suite right in the heart of downtown.
 
There are paid parking lots nearby, or we can arrange parking for you at the building for $25 per day, with advance notice at the time of booking. You will always have an ample supply of towels, a hair dryer, high speed wireless, and cable TV. Make sure to draw the curtains and enjoy the in-home movie projector!

The entire suite is at your disposal, as well as the gym on the 12th floor and rooftop patio. Parties are not allowed at the building or in the suite. Our children also stay here with us at times, please do not smoke or do any illegal drugs in our home. Note that our belongings remain in the suite, stored out of your way. Please be respectful and do not touch items which are not left out in the open or identified as for guest use during check-in.

We travel ourselves, and love meeting all kinds of interesting people from all around the world. We are always happy to chat when we give you the keys and go over the house rules, and we love giving our recommendations if you have any questions about Toronto.

Our neighbourhood is the heart of Entertainment District, TIFF, CN tower just couple mins away from the condo.

You can also take a subway, taxi, train or uber from here.

Please take off your shoes when you are in the unit. 
Please check with us before doing laundry. We charge $3 per load which includes the use of the washer, dryer, or drying rack, detergent, and dryer sheets.
No shoes or odd items are allowed to be washed in the machines - normal fabric clothing only.

Check out time is 11:00 am. Late check out will be charge for $10 per hour.
